From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Petr=20=C5=A0tetiar?= <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Date: Fri, 26 Apr 2024 06:41:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] scripts: tr181-xpon.sh: make core size configurable
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CI currently reports, that component has unlimited core size enabled:

 ERROR: unlimited core size detected: tr181-xpon -D

So lets fix it by making it disabled by default and configurable via
/etc/environment and thus keep in sync with other prplWare components.

Fixes: PCF-1188
References: PCF-663
References: https://gitlab.com/prpl-foundation/prplos/prplos/-/jobs/6719417516#L133
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
 scripts/tr181-xpon.sh | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/scripts/tr181-xpon.sh b/scripts/tr181-xpon.sh
index 20ff26edd604..691e8fd4b768 100644
--- a/scripts/tr181-xpon.sh
+++ b/scripts/tr181-xpon.sh
@@ -1,5 +1,8 @@
 #!/bin/sh
-ulimit -c unlimited
+
+[ -f /etc/environment ] && . /etc/environment
+# shellcheck disable=SC3045
+ulimit -c "${ULIMIT_CONFIGURATION:-0}"
 name="tr181-xpon"
 
 proxypath="Device.XPON."
@@ -12,7 +15,7 @@ function tr181_mapping () {
 
 case $1 in
     start|boot)
-        source /etc/environment
+        . /etc/environment
         tr181_mapping &
         ${name} -D
         ;;
